## Upcoming Feature: Network Configuration

We are excited to announce that the upcoming release of CentOS 9 will include enhanced network configuration options. This new feature will provide administrators with more flexibility and control over their network settings.

Key features of the Network Configuration module include:

- Advanced IP address management
- Support for VLANs and virtual interfaces
- Improved network bonding and teaming options
- Enhanced firewall configuration

Stay tuned for the official release of CentOS 9, where we will provide detailed documentation on how to leverage these new network configuration capabilities.

If you have any questions or feedback, please don't hesitate to reach out to our support team.